Virtual Machines play a critical role in disaster recovery (DR) by enabling replication and failover of workloads.

For example, an organization can replicate its on-premise servers to Azure VMs. In case of a disaster, workloads can be quickly switched to Azure.

A real-life use case is a financial institution ensuring business continuity during outages or natural disasters.

Another example is data center failure, where applications can be restored on Azure VMs within minutes.

Azure Site Recovery is commonly used to automate this process.

VM-based disaster recovery ensures minimal downtime and data loss.
